Bring a large #pot{} of generously salted water to a boil. Add @farro{3/4%cup}; cook until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Drain and return farro to pot. Stir in @mushroom stock concentrate{2}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

While farro cooks, preheat a well-oiled #grill{} to medium-high heat. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6}; trim ends from @scallions{6}; peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced); halve @thyme{1/4%ounce} sprigs crosswise; zest and quarter @lemon{1}; slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

In a large #bowl{}, toss asparagus and scallions with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon}, a big pinch of salt, and pepper. Set aside.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine garlic, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, half the thyme sprigs, and @olive oil{3%tbsp}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to infuse.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, half the lemon zest, juice from two lemon wedges, and @olive oil{2%tbsp} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and remaining garlic powder; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from heat.

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Add steak and marinated veggies to grill. Grill steak to desired doneness, ~{4-8%minutes} per side. Grill veggies, turning occasionally, until slightly charred and tender, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> Grills can vary for cooking times.

Remove from heat. Transfer steak to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

> PAN ALTERNATIVE: Cook marinated veggies in a large oiled pan over medium-high heat until charred and tender, 4-6 minutes. Transfer to a plate. If pan is dry, add a drizzle of oil. Cook steak in same pan over medium-high heat, 5-7 minutes per side (work in batches for 4).

While steak rests, remove thyme sprigs from garlic oil; discard thyme sprigs. Whisk in @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, remaining lemon zest, and juice from remaining lemon until smooth and combined; season with salt and pepper. Reserve 1 TBSP dressing for serving.

Slice asparagus and scallions into 2-inch pieces; add to pot with drained farro. Stir in mushrooms and remaining dressing. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice steak against the grain.

Spread ricotta in an even layer across bottoms of shallow #bowls{}. Spoon farro salad over ricotta and top with steak. Drizzle reserved dressing over steak and serve.